Elytra (
Fig. 4A
):

Approximately 2.5× longer and 1.1× wider than pronotum; 
striae:
narrower than interstriae, marked by circular punctures, on dorsal striae smaller than that on lateral striae; 
epipleura
with setae on region closest to the humeri which have a tuft of long setae.
